                    <note>
                        <ab type="description">There are two rivers known by the name ʾAngarab. This
                            record refers to the so-called Great ʾAngarab (cfr. <placeName ref="LOC1452Angara">Small ʾAngarab</placeName>), a tributary of the
                                <placeName ref="LOC1598Atbara">ʾAtbārā</placeName>. It rises north
                            of <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName>, near <placeName ref="LOC2580Dawa">Dāwā</placeName> in <placeName ref="LOC6144Wagara">Wagarā</placeName>. It flows west through <placeName ref="LOC1537Armace">ʾArmāč̣ǝho</placeName>, along the border between
                                <placeName ref="LOC6144Wagara">Wagarā</placeName> and <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName>
                            <placeName>ʾawrāǧǧās</placeName>.</ab>
